open_houses.description: Romantic, Emotional, Vintage convey estate's 1930s storybook cottage pedigree. Compound presides at the pinnacle of the Sunset Strip & offers breathtaking views of Downtown Los Angeles & Pacific Ocean. Main House includes 3BRs/2BAs w/ add'l 1BR/1BA guest apt & detached 2sty 1BR/1BA casita w/kitchen Total sq ft is over 3,000. All offer separate entrances, a perfect setup for add'l income. Rugged posts & beams, peg & groove floor, antique doors from a European hotel, stately fireplace & floor to ceiling windows create impressive entertaining spaces. Newly renovated kitchen w/ built-in breakfast area seating. Lounge in an oversized primary steam shower while gazing at the ocean or find quiet contemplation in the estate's vaulted reading tower. 2 private entertaining patios & a 2-car garage complete this eclectic paradise. Located in award winning Wonderland Elementary & near prominent Hollywood locales: Soho Club, The Whiskey, Saddle Ranch, Comedy Store, The Edition, & Sunset Tower.

1939 Traditional 4 bedroom/4 bathroom home on two lots. The three levels provide flexibility for families and/or perfect setting for working from home. The first floor has two bedrooms/one bathroom currently set up as a guest suite with kitchenette. This level also has a family room, fireplace, and wet bar. Second level has a large living room with fireplace, dining room, remodeled kitchen with custom cabinetry, Sub-Zero refrigerator, restored vintage stove, separate breakfast room or den, gym/office and bathroom. Outside the kitchen is a private deck perfect for al fresco dining. Upper level has two bedroom suites. The primary suite, with remodeled bathroom, has a screened in veranda with built in sectional and serene views. Grounds provide custom secure wrought iron rails/gates, lush landscaping, separate studio with electricity, lemon, fig, and blood orange trees. Direct access two car garage. Two separate HVAC systems, security system, sonos, and much more.

This single story Ranch style home in Woodland Hills boasts loads of curb appeal. Upon arriving to this Carleton Terrace property you instantly notice the long driveway and tall palm trees. This 1,653 square foot Mid Century house has a traditional style floor plan with four bedrooms and two full bathrooms. There is a large open great room with a fireplace that connects to the dining area and eat-in kitchen. The dining area opens up to the backyard with large sliding glass doors. The galley style kitchen is sizable and flows from the dining area into the eat-in area. The backyard has ample patio space, and features views to the side, of the valley, tree tops, and distant mountains. This home is just minutes from The Village, and all the incredible amenities Woodland Hills has to offer. Incredible opportunity to make this home your own and add value.

Located on a fabulous street in Highland Park, just up the road from all the great restaurants, shops and bars on the ever so desirable Figueroa St. This 3 Bed + 3 Bath has a desirable open floor plan, with vaulted ceilings and views of lush green trees out every window, allowing for an abundance of natural light throughout. An oversized sun deck off the upstairs living space is perfect for BBQ, indoor/outdoor entertaining, or enjoying a cup of coffee in the morning or a glass a wine at night. Overlooking the homes large and open backyard, accompanied by mature trees, truly creates a private oasis. Downstairs you'll find 3 beds + 2 baths, with the primary having its own ensuite bath and two of the three bedrooms having private balcony's facing the backyard. This is certainly not to be missed! So much potential in this tranquil, hillside home!
